      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 2) REASON about structure\u2013activity relationships (why features matter)\nCYP2D6 inhibition commonly correlates with:\n- A **protonatable basic N** (pKa often ~7\u201310) that can form a **salt bridge / ionic interaction** with acidic residues in the CYP2D6 active site (classically Asp301), plus\n- One or more **aromatic/hydrophobic regions** to occupy lipophilic pockets.",
