      "content": "### 3) CONSIDER mechanistic basis (interaction with CYP2D6)\nMany CYP inhibitors bind by:\n- **Type II coordination** (heteroatom lone pair coordinating heme iron) \u2014 common for **imidazoles/triazoles** (e.g., antifungals) and can yield broad CYP inhibition.\n- **CYP2D6-specific binding** often relies more on the **basic amine\u2013Asp301 interaction** plus hydrophobic packing.",
